               <p>1794. <persName id="def1-1794-18440610" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1794-18440610" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1794-18440610" type="age" value="26"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1794-18440610" type="surname" value="FRYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1794-18440610" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN FRYER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18440610-1794-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440610-1794-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440610-1794-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing 1 cash-box, value 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 sovereign, 73 shillings, 33 sixpences, and 19 groats; the property of <persName id="t18440610-name-1396" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1396" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1396" type="surname" value="HODGES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1396" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440610-1794-offence-1 t18440610-name-1396"></join>George Hodges</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1397" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1397" type="surname" value="HODGES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1397" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HODGES</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a beer-shop—the prisoner was my waiter—I had a cash-box, about the 7th of June, in the counter in the bar—I missed it—there were books and papers in it, a sovereign, and about 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in shillings, sixpences, and fourpenny pieces—I went to the station, brought an officer, gave all my people in charge to the officer, while I and another person went to look over my premises—and in a lobby of the water-closet, I found the box broken open—the books and papers were left in it, but the money was gone—I called the policeman—he took the box from there, and from what Miller said, I gave the prisoner into custody—I searched further, and found 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in a little piece of rag under the stairs—I had seen my box safe at a quarter-past four, and missed it at six o'clock—the pri<lb></lb>soner was there, and thirteen or fourteen other persons.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1398" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1398" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1398" type="given" value="JACOB"></interp>JACOB MILLER</persName>
                  </hi>. At half-past five o'clock on the 7th of June, I went to one of the water-closets, I saw it was dirty—I went to the others to see that they were clean—I then went out, shut the door, and sat down just outside the closet—I saw the prisoner come round and go into the water-closet, and shut the door—I then heard a stamping on the floor, and as if a box or some<lb></lb>thing was rattling, and five or six kicks—the prisoner then came out and passed by where I was—he said, "Halloo"—I said, "I am having a <hi rend="italic">pitch</hi>"—he passed by, and came again in about five minutes; he said, "I have got <hi rend="italic">a slice of luck</hi>"—I said, "What is it?"—he said, "I have found 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and we will go and have a glass of gin"—we went and had it—I came back and</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184406100211"></xptr>
               <p>went to take checks at the gate—while I was there, Mr. Hodges came and said, "Come with me"—we were all called in, and the policeman came in—Mr. Hodges said, "I have lost my cash-box"—I said to the prisoner, "<hi rend="italic">Jack</hi> you are the man, I heard you breaking the box open"—no one could have gone into that water-closet without my seeing it—the box was found in that water-closet.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> When you saw me go in, were you not smoking a pipe? <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, I was leaning against the water-closet—you might have had the box under your coat, I could only see your head—I never knew a stain on your character before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1399" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1399" type="surname" value="HOCKADAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1399" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL HOCKADAY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 178.) I found this cash-box in the lobby of the water-closet—I found the cash in this cloth under the stairs.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1400" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1400" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1400" type="given" value="JACOB"></interp>JACOB MILLER</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I had been sitting down with the prisoner in the fore part of the week, and he opened this napkin, which had his dinner wrapped in it—I noticed it as being a napkin, and this piece, that the money was wrapped in is part of the same napkin.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> There were twenty persons on the premises, and they had equal opportunity of getting to the bar as myself.</p>
               <p>
